# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:3298
msgid "BASH can be tweaked to change its glob behavior with its shopt builtin options such as \"<literal>dotglob</literal>\", \"<literal>noglob</literal>\", \"<literal>nocaseglob</literal>\", \"<literal>nullglob</literal>\", \"<literal>nocaseglob</literal>\", \"<literal>extglob</literal>\", etc.  See <literal>bash</literal>(1)."
