"Package: equivs\n"
"Priority: extra\n"
"Section: admin\n"
"Description: Circumventing Debian package dependencies\n"
" This is a dummy package which can be used to create Debian\n"
" packages, which only contain dependency information."
msgstr ""

#: debian-reference.en.xml:7922
msgid "Port a package to the stable system"
msgstr "安定版システムへのパッケージ移植"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:7923
msgid "For partial upgrades of the <literal>stable</literal> system, rebuilding a package within its environment using the source package is desirable.  This avoids massive package upgrades due to their dependencies.  First, add the following entries to the \"<literal>/etc/apt/sources.list</literal>\" of a <literal>stable</literal> system:"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:7924
#, no-wrap
msgid "deb-src http://http.us.debian.org/debian unstable  main contrib non-free"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:7925
msgid "Then get the required packages and the source to be downloaded and compiled by:"
