# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:8820
msgid "For example, \"<literal>/etc/default/hotplug</literal>\" can be used to control how \"<literal>/etc/init.d/hotplug</literal>\" works.  The \"<literal>/etc/default/rcS</literal>\" file can be used to customize boot-time defaults for <literal>motd</literal>(5), <literal>sulogin</literal>(8), etc."
