# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:12282
msgid "For more specific examples of custom network configuration scripts using these environment variables, you should check example scripts in \"<literal>/usr/share/doc/ifupdown/examples/*</literal>\" and scripts used in <literal>ifscheme</literal> and <literal>ifupdown-scripts-zg2</literal> packages.  These additional scripts have some overlaps of functinalities with basic <literal>ifupdown-extra</literal> and <literal>guessnet</literal> packages.  If you install these additional scripts, you should customize these scripts to avoid interferences."
