#: debian-reference.en.xml:21504
msgid "Chroot system"
msgstr "Chrootシステム"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21505
msgid "<literal>chroot</literal>(8) is most basic way to run different instances of the GNU/Linux environment on a single system simultaneously without rebooting. I will explain simple <ulink url=\"&chroot;\">chroot</ulink> systems in the following as examples."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21507
msgid "Examples below assumes both parent system and chroot system share the same CPU architecture."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21509
msgid "For serious chroot setup with the detail configuration, such as <literal>i386</literal> chroot system under <literal>amd64</literal> parent system, please consider to use the specialized <literal>schroot</literal> package."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21511
msgid "Run a different Debian distribution with chroot"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21512
msgid "A chroot Debian environment can easily be created by <literal>debootstrap</literal>(8) or <literal>cdebootstrap</literal>(1)."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21513
msgid "For example, the following will create a <literal>sid</literal> chroot on \"<literal>/sid-root</literal>\" while having fast Internet access:"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21514
#, no-wrap
msgid "main # debootstrap sid /sid-root http://ftp.debian.org/debian/"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21518
msgid "watch it download the whole system"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21522
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"main # echo \"proc-sid    /sid-root/proc     proc   none 0 0\" &gt;&gt; /etc/fstab\n"
"main # echo \"devpts-sid  /sid-root/dev/pts  devpts defaults 0 0\" &gt;&gt; /etc/fstab\n"
"main # mount -a\n"
"main # cp -f /etc/passwd /sid-root/etc/passwd\n"
"main # cp -f /etc/shadow /sid-root/etc/shadow\n"
"main # cp -f /etc/group  /sid-root/etc/group\n"
"main # cp -f /etc/hosts  /sid-root/etc/hosts\n"
"main # chroot /sid-root /bin/bash\n"
"chroot # cd /dev; /sbin/MAKEDEV generic ; cd -\n"
"chroot # vi /etc/apt/sources.list"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21535
msgid "point the source to unstable"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21539
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"chroot # aptitude update\n"
"...\n"
"chroot # aptitude install locales\n"
"..."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21546
msgid "add \"en_US.UTF-8\" as locale and make it default"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21550
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Do you want to continue? [Y/n/?] y\n"
"chroot # aptitude install mc vim\n"
"...\n"
"Do you want to continue? [Y/n/?] y\n"
"...\n"
"chroot # exit\n"
"main #"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21557
msgid "At this point you should have a fully working Debian sid system, where you can play around without fear of affecting your main Debian installation."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21559
msgid "If you use bind mount for directories such as home directory in the chroot, you must be careful for its side effects.  I heard people lost their home directory after executing \"<literal>rm -rf /sid-root</literal>\" <emphasis role=\"strong\">without unbinding</emphasis> their home directory in the chroot. A <emphasis role=\"strong\">bind mount</emphasis> is not normally visible with <literal>df</literal>(1), you need to execute \"<literal>df -a</literal>\" to see it."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21561
msgid "This <literal>debootstrap</literal> trick can also be used to <ulink url=\"&installdebian;\">install Debian</ulink> to a system without using a Debian install disk, but instead from another GNU/Linux distribution."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21564
msgid "Setting up login for chroot"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21565
msgid "Typing \"<literal>chroot /sid-root /bin/bash</literal>\" is easy, but it retains all sorts of environment variables that you may not want, and has other issues.  A much better approach is to run another login process on a separate virtual terminal where you can log in to the chroot directly."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21566
msgid "Since on default Debian systems <literal>tty1</literal> to <literal>tty6</literal> run Linux consoles and <literal>tty7</literal> runs the X Window System, let's set up <literal>tty8</literal> for a chrooted console as an example.  After creating a chroot system, type from the root shell of the main system:"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21567
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"main # echo \"8:23:respawn:/usr/sbin/chroot /sid-root /sbin/getty 38400 tty8\"  &gt;&gt; /etc/inittab\n"
"main # init q"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21572
msgid "reload init"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21578
msgid "Setting up X for chroot"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21579
msgid "You want to run the latest X and GNOME safely in your chroot? That's entirely possible! The following example will make GDM run on virtual terminal <literal>vt9</literal>."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21580
msgid "First install a chroot system.  From the root of the main system, copy key configuration files to the chroot system."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21581
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"main # cp /etc/X11/xorg.conf /sid-root/etc/X11/xorg.conf\n"
"main # chroot /sid-root\n"
"chroot # cd /dev; /sbin/MAKEDEV generic ; cd -\n"
"chroot # aptitude install gdm gnome x-window-system\n"
"chroot # vim /etc/gdm/gdm.conf"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21589
msgid "change \"<literal>[servers]</literal>\" section with \"<literal>s/vt7/vt9/</literal>\" to make the first virtual console in the chroot from <literal>vt7</literal> to <literal>vt9</literal>."
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21593
#, no-wrap
msgid "chroot # /etc/init.d/gdm start"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21594
msgid "Now you can easily switch back and forth between full X environments in your chroot and your main system just by switching between Linux virtual terminals; e.g.  by using Ctrl-Alt-F7 and Ctrl-Alt-F9.  Have fun!"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21597
msgid "Run other distributions with chroot"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21598
msgid "A chroot environment for another Linux distribution can easily be created. You install a system into separate partitions using the installer of the other distribution.  If its root partition is in \"<literal>/dev/hda9</literal>\":"
msgstr ""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xml:21599
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"main # cd / ; mkdir /other-dist\n"
"main # mount -t ext3 /dev/hda9 /other-dist\n"
"main # chroot /other-dist /bin/bash"
msgstr ""

